{"type":"message","id":"71fdd719","parentId":"6d552b18","timestamp":"2026-04-14T17:24:46.185Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_xoowdbixyzqz_1","toolName":"sessions_history","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"sessionKey\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31\",\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"[cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31 5p Progress Report — AHV DTLX/QLHV] You are the 5-minute change-detecting reporter for the AHV DTLX (Đào Tạo Lái Xe) ecosystem.\\n\\nCheck sessions_list. Compare current active sessions against the last known state stored in memory/heartbeat-state.json.\\n\\n**If nothing has changed since the last report:**\\n- Stay SILENT. Send nothing. Not even HEARTBEAT_OK. Just exit quietly.\\n\\n**If there IS a change** (new session spawned, session died, agent failed, task started/completed, blocker appeared), compose a concise change report to group -5163901258:\\n\\nFormat:\\n🟡 Orbis-DTLX — 5p Update | {HH:MM} UTC {DD MMM}\\n\\nChanges detected:\\n• [list of actual changes]\\n\\nPipeline: {HEALTHY if no failures / DEGRADED if failures}\\n• Active sessions: N\\n• MCP: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅\\n\\nOnly send when something changed. Stay silent when stable.\\nCurrent time: Tuesday, April 14th, 2026 - 5:20 PM (UTC) / 2026-04-14 17:20 UTC\\n\\nReturn your summary as plain text; it will be delivered automatically. If the task explicitly calls for messaging a specific external recipient, note who/where it should go instead of sending it yourself.\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"timestamp\": 1776187259536,\n      \"__openclaw\": {\n        \"id\": \"0ca7aa89\",\n        \"seq\": 1\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"Let me check the sessions_list and compare against the last known state stored in memory/heartbeat-state.json.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_function_brt1p5fcast3_1\",\n          \"name\": \"sessions_list\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"kinds\": [\n              \"agent\"\n            ],\n            \"messageLimit\": 2\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_function_brt1p5fcast3_2\",\n          \"name\": \"read\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"path\": \"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/memory/heartbeat-state.json\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n      \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1776187259714,\n      \"responseId\": \"062daa7d6eae2cca6549e5ad82128975\",\n      \"__openclaw\": {\n        \"id\": \"4a449b74\",\n        \"seq\": 2\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"Now let me compare the current session state against the last known state from heartbeat-state.json.\\n\\n**Last known state (17:06 UTC):**\\n- `cron:ed2d0b5d` — running (5p QLHV monitor)\\n- `cron:6f3323ef` — running (5p DTLX monitor)\\n- `cron:e7885813` — running (Agent Status to Lead) — had 1 consecutive error, zombie cleared\\n- Pipeline: DEGRADED\\n\\n**Current state (17:20 UTC):**\\n- `cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31` — **running** ✅ (this very cron session)\\n\\n\\n- `cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e` — **running** but showing an aborted error with \\\"Request was aborted\\\" and 6 messages, suggesting it ran for about 4 minutes before failing\\n- `telegram:group:-5163901258` — **done** (ended at 1776163783190), replaced by the DTLX group session which is still running since 1776163408296\\n- `telegram:direct:6053576134` — **done** (ended at 1776162158012)\\n- `cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7` — **done** (ended at 1776186124500)\\n- `agent:master-orchestrator:main` — **done**\\n\\nSo the running sessions at 17:20 are just `cron:6f3323ef` and `cron:e7885813`, with the DTLX group running since 06:36 UTC but marked as done. Comparing this to the 17:06 state, the `cron:e7885813` session is still active but showing the aborted error from around 17:11 UTC, while the others have all completed. So `cron:e7885813` is still running but just got aborted mid-execution, which could mean it's retrying or waiting for the next cycle. Looking at the status report from 17:16, it shows 3 active sessions (the DTLX cron, the Agent Status cron that just fired, and the DTLX group monitor), and that was already marked as healthy with no issues.\\n\\nNow I'm checking if the pipeline has actually changed since the last state snapshot at 17:06. The key change I'm seeing is that `cron:e7885813` ran for about a minute starting at 17:17 UTC and got aborted, but the consecutive errors counter was at 1 before that, so I need to verify whether this abortion represents a new error or just the normal cycle ending.\\n\\nLooking at the other sessions, `cron:ed2d0b5d` has finished its run and is marked as done, and the DTLX group is still running normally. Since there are no new failures beyond what was already tracked and the pipeline status remains healthy, this appears to be a stable state with no significant changes to report. 3 sessions (cron:6f3323ef ✅, cron:e7885813 ✅, telegram:group:-5163901258 ✅)\\n- `cron:e7885813` had 1 error, but now it's reactivated and running (zombie cleared)\\n\\nThe only real change between the 17:06 and 17:20 snapshots is `cron:ed2d0b5d` finishing, which aligns with the 17:14 report mentioning it completed around 17:08. Since the last update already captured that completion, there's nothing new to report here—the pipeline's still healthy and stable. I'm tracing through the actual timestamps more carefully now. The heartbeat state file shows 17:06, but looking at the session data, the cron:e7885813 actually ended at 17:12:02 with an aborted error, not 17:16 as I thought. Let me verify the exact sequence of events across these sessions to get the timing right. I'm noticing that `cron:e7885813` shows as running in the heartbeat state from 17:06, but the session itself ended with an aborted error at 17:12 — this suggests the cron job re-triggered after that error and is currently running again, which matches what the 17:16 status report showed. Now I need to trace back what the heartbeat state looked like before 17:06 to understand the full sequence. Looking at the `cron:e7885813` session, it ended with an abort error after running for about 78 seconds, but the system still considers it \\\"running\\\" in the heartbeat state because the cron job itself is active and will likely retry. The recent 17:16 status report shows all three critical sessions running with the pipeline healthy, so there's no state change to report. I'm realizing the heartbeat state file I'm looking at is from an earlier check at 17:06, but the most recent status report was sent at 17:16 \\n…(truncated)…\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"Comparing current state (17:20 UTC) against the heartbeat-state baseline (17:06 UTC) and the last 5p report (17:14 UTC):\\n\\n- `cron:6f3323ef` DTLX — still running ✅\\n- `cron:e7885813` Agent Status — still running ✅ (aborted at 17:12, reactivated)\\n- `telegram:group:-5163901258` — still active ✅\\n- `cron:ed2d0b5d` — completed (already noted at 17:14)\\n- No new failures, no new blockers, no state transitions\\n\\n**No change from last stable state. Silent exit.**\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n      \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1776187269852,