DTLX cron, the Agent Status cron that just fired, and the DTLX group monitor), and that was already marked as healthy with no issues.\n\nNow I'm checking if the pipeline has actually changed since the last state snapshot at 17:06. The key change I'm seeing is that `cron:e7885813` ran for about a minute starting at 17:17 UTC and got aborted, but the consecutive errors counter was at 1 before that, so I need to verify whether this abortion represents a new error or just the normal cycle ending.\n\nLooking at the other sessions, `cron:ed2d0b5d` has finished its run and is marked as done, and the DTLX group is still running normally. Since there are no new failures beyond what was already tracked and the pipeline status remains healthy, this appears to be a stable state with no significant changes to report. 3 sessions (cron:6f3323ef ✅, cron:e7885813 ✅, telegram:group:-5163901258 ✅)\n- `cron:e7885813` had 1 error, but now it's reactivated and running (zombie cleared)\n\nThe only real change between the 17:06 and 17:20 snapshots is `cron:ed2d0b5d` finishing, which aligns with the 17:14 report mentioning it completed around 17:08. Since the last update already captured that completion, there's nothing new to report here—the pipeline's still healthy and stable. I'm tracing through the actual timestamps more carefully now. The heartbeat state file shows 17:06, but looking at the session data, the cron:e7885813 actually ended at 17:12:02 with an aborted error, not 17:16 as I thought. Let me verify the exact sequence of events across these sessions to get the timing right. I'm noticing that `cron:e7885813` shows as running in the heartbeat state from 17:06, but the session itself ended with an aborted error at 17:12 — this suggests the cron job re-triggered after that error and is currently running again, which matches what the 17:16 status report showed. Now I need to trace back what the heartbeat state looked like before 17:06 to understand the full sequence. Looking at the `cron:e7885813` session, it ended with an abort error after running for about 78 seconds, but the system still considers it \"running\" in the heartbeat state because the cron job itself is active and will likely retry. The recent 17:16 status report shows all three critical sessions running with the pipeline healthy, so there's no state change to report. I'm realizing the heartbeat state file I'm looking at is from an earlier check at 17:06, but the most recent status report was sent at 17:16 \n…(truncated)…"},{"type":"text","text":"Comparing current state (17:20 UTC) against the heartbeat-state baseline (17:06 UTC) and the last 5p report (17:14 UTC):\n\n- `cron:6f3323ef` DTLX — still running ✅\n- `cron:e7885813` Agent Status — still running ✅ (aborted at 17:12, reactivated)\n- `telegram:group:-5163901258` — still active ✅\n- `cron:ed2d0b5d` — completed (already noted at 17:14)\n- No new failures, no new blockers, no state transitions\n\n**No change from last stable state. Silent exit.**"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776187269852,"responseId":"062daa86e61456f3f2bde5f8f83ca71a","__openclaw":{"id":"694c6d9b","seq":5}}],"truncated":true,"droppedMessages":false,"contentTruncated":true,"contentRedacted":false,"bytes":6886},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776187486183}}
{"type":"message","id":"cdbcf2d8","parentId":"71fdd719","timestamp":"2026-04-14T17:25:05.111Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture. Let me also check the heartbeat-state more carefully to understand what changed from 17:06 to now.\n\n**Baseline (17:06 UTC):**\n- `cron:ed2d0b5d` — running (5p QLHV)\n- `cron:6f3323ef` — running (5p DTLX)\n- `cron:e7885813` — running (Agent Status to Lead), 1 consecutive error (note: \"was aborted at 16:40, reactivated 17:06 — zombie cleared\")\n- Pipeline: DEGRADED\n- Blockers: cron:e7885813 — reactivated, 1 consecutive error\n\n\n- \nNow looking at the current state at 17:23, the 5p QLHV cron has finished as expected, but the e7885813 error is still persisting—it aborted again at 17:12:02, which means it's accumulating consecutive errors and now showing 2 failures total. So `cron:e7885813` actually failed twice in the same session—it aborted once at 16:40 and again at 17:12, which means it's accumulated 2 consecutive errors. The heartbeat state from 17:06 cleared the zombie after the first failure, but then the second abort happened 6 minutes later, and by 17:16 the session was marked as running again, suggesting it reactivated.\n\nLooking at the current state at 17:23, the session is still running with that same session ID, which means it's been continuously active since 17:06 despite those two aborts. The status report from 17:16 only mentioned the 16:40 error, so the 17:12 failure wasn't reflected there yet.\n\nNow comparing to the baseline from 17:06, the picture becomes clearer: the 5p QLHV monitor finished normally at 17:08, the Agent Status cron hit its second abort and accumulated 2 consecutive errors, and the DTLX monitor and group session remained stable throughout.\n\nLooking at the 17:16 report versus where we are now at 17:23, the key difference is that e7885813's error count went from 1 to 2—those two consecutive timeouts at 16:40 and 17:12 mean the Agent Status to Lead cron should have stopped delivery, but I need to figure out why that didn't happen or if there's a different mechanism at play.\n\nThe current heartbeat state still shows DEGRADED with e7885813 flagged as having 1 consecutive error, but that's outdated now since we've hit 2 failures. I should update the heartbeat state to reflect the new DEGRADED status and notify the Lead, though I'm noticing the previous heartbeat already acknowledged e7885813's recovery attempt, which contradicts the current failure count.\n\nLooking at the sessions list, cron:e7885813 is marked as running, but the actual session shows an \"aborted\" status. This suggests the session is a cron wrapper that stays active between executions while the underlying task aborts and restarts—so the abort at 17:12 is probably just a single failed execution within an ongoing retry loop.\n\nSince e7885813 has now accumulated 2 consecutive failures, I should update the heartbeat state to reflect DEGRADED status with this new blocker, then send a notification about the change.","thinkingSignature":"befe1a098be3cf7a249b56b53efce78c5d22ba8d5b138f3454896cffcf834d88"},{"type":"text","text":"**State change detected — updating heartbeat state and sending report:**\n\n- `cron:e7885813`: 2nd consecutive abort (17:12) — pipeline DEGRADED, needs review\n- `cron:ed2d0b5d`: completed normally (already resolved)\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kydjhwlmphqd_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/memory/heartbeat-state.json","content":"{\n  \"lastChecked\": \"2026-04-14T17:23:00Z\",\n  \"sessions\": {\n    \"cron:ed2d0b5d\": { \"status\": \"done\", \"label\": \"5p QLHV monitor\", \"note\": \"completed normally 17:08 UTC\" },\n    \"cron:6f3323ef\": { \"status\": \"running\", \"label\": \"5p DTLX monitor\", \"consecutiveErrors\": 0 },\n    \"cron:e7885813\": { \"status\": \"running\", \"label\": \"Agent Status to Lead\", \"consecutiveErrors\": 2, \"note\": \"aborted at 16:40 + 17:12 — delivery may be stopped per 2-error threshold\" }\n  },\n  \"zombies\": [],\n  \"pipeline\": \"DEGRADED\",\n  \"blockers\": [\"cron:e7885813 — 2 consecutive aborts, delivery stopped. Needs review: fix, disable, or adjust error threshold.\"]\n}\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":2298,"output":1028,"cacheRead":26268,"cacheWrite":2359,"totalTokens":31953,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776187486188,"responseId":"062dab5fc46a756a9d7b02734435c5ae"}}
